AU  - Clayton, Christopher
AU  - Schaab, Andreas
T1  - Bail-Ins, Optimal Regulation, and Crisis Resolution
PY  - 2025
Y1  - 2025/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhaf002
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 38
IS  - 9
SP  - 2810
EP  - 2843
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We develop a tractable dynamic contracting framework to study bank bail-in regimes. In the presence of a repeated monitoring problem, the optimal bank capital structure combines standard debt, which induces liquidation and provides strong incentives, and bail-in debt, which restores solvency but provides weaker incentives. Given fire sales, an optimal policy response entails joint regulation: a bail-in regime reduces standard debt while leverage regulation reduces total debt. Bail-ins replace bailouts as a recapitalization tool.
Y2  - 4/28/2026
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhaf002
ER  - 




